'''Yin Fire Rooster also known as 丁酉''' (hinototori, teika no tori, teiyuu) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}.

It is the 34th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}, preceded by {{ill|Bingshen|ja|丙申}} and followed by {{ill|Wuxu|ja|戊戌}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} symbol {{ill|Tei|ja|丁}} represents yin {{ill|Fire|ja|火}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}} symbol {{ill|Rooster|ja|酉}} represents yin {{ill|Metal|ja|金}}, establishing a restraining relationship ({{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）}}) (i.e. Fire overcomes Metal).

==辛亥の年==
A year in the {{ill|Western calendar|ja|西暦}} that leaves a remainder of 51 when divided by 60 is a {{ill|year|ja|年}} of {{ill|Xinhai|ja|辛亥}}.
