'''Yin Fire Rooster also known as 丁酉''' (hinototori, teika no tori, teiyuu) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}.

It is the 34th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}, preceded by {{ill|Bingshen|ja|丙申}} and followed by {{ill|Wuxu|ja|戊戌}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and the Five Phases}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} symbol {{ill|Tei|ja|丁|1=Hinoto (丁)}} represents yin {{ill|Fire|ja|火}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}} symbol {{ill|Rooster|ja|酉|1=Rooster (zodiac)|lt=Rooster (酉)}} represents yin {{ill|Metal|ja|金}}, establishing a restraining relationship ({{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）}}) (i.e. Fire overcomes Metal).

