'''Yin Fire Rooster also known as 丁酉''' (hinototori, teika no tori, teiyuu) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}.

It is the 34th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, preceded by {{ill|Bingshen|ja|丙申|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} and followed by {{ill|Wuxu|ja|戊戌|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} symbol {{ill|Tei|ja|丁|1=Hinoto (丁)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} represents yin {{ill|Fire|ja|火|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} symbol {{ill|Rooster|ja|酉|1=Rooster (zodiac)|2=ja|3=酉|4=fr|5=Coq (astrologie chinoise)|6=nl|7=Haan (astrologie)|lt=Rooster (酉)|1=Rooster (zodiac)|lt=Rooster (酉)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} represents yin {{ill|Metal|ja|金|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, establishing a restraining relationship ({{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}) (i.e. Fire overcomes Metal).

